Hi Sean,

Yes, the magic square is a potential starting point. That would probably be=
 enough for a semester project. I have a bigger goal in the background, I c=
an tell you about that too.

If you're curious, here is an example of a recent paper that was written de=
tailing a small group's experience with formalizing a quantum information p=
roof in Lean https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.08672. For us, the project would be=
 smaller and we would keep a flavor of cryptography. Here is what is alread=
y written about the CHSH game in mathlib: https://leanprover-community.gith=
ub.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Star/CHSH.html#CHSH_id

We can talk the same time on Thursday (3pm), or Wednesday at 14h30 or Frida=
y at 14h?

Thomas
