From: Sean Perazzolo <sean.perazzolo@epfl.ch>
Sent: Monday, November 17, 2025 8:00 AM
To: Thomas Vidick <thomas.vidick@epfl.ch>
Subject: Follow-up: Lean project for MS research

Dear Professor Vidick,

Thank you for meeting with us last week.

The semester project on formally verifying proofs using Lean, though challe=
nging, has definitely sparked my interest. I am particularly interested in =
its potential to contribute to the community and to link my knowledge of qu=
antum mechanics with computer science.

From our discussion, I understood you are interested in verifying proofs in=
 Lean that have not yet been formalized, such as the Mermin and Peres Magic=
 Square.

I have been exploring the subject the last few days and believe there is gr=
eat potential here, possibly even for a research project for my MS in Cyber=
security.

Could we meet again this week to talk more about this idea?

Best regards,
Sean Perazzolo

